  "prompt": "What is the best way to substitute celery seeds in a recipe?",
  "response": "If you need to substitute celery seeds in a recipe, here are several options:\n\n1. **Celery Salt**: This is a common substitute, but it is saltier than celery seeds. Use it in a 1:1 ratio, but reduce the amount of any additional salt in the recipe to taste.\n\n2. **Fresh Celery**: If you have fresh celery on hand, you can chop it finely and use it in place of celery seeds. About 2 tablespoons of finely chopped fresh celery can replace 1 teaspoon of celery seeds. \n\n3. **Caraway Seeds**: These have a somewhat similar flavor profile and can be used as a substitute in equal amounts.\n\n4. **Dill Seeds**: They can offer a slightly different flavor but work well in many recipes, especially in pickling or salad dressings. Use them in equal amounts.\n\n5. **Fennel Seeds**: These have a sweeter flavor than celery seeds but can be a decent replacement in certain dishes.\n\n6. **Parsley and a Bit of Salt**: This combination can mimic the green flavor of celery. Use 1 tablespoon of fresh parsley and a pinch of salt for each teaspoon of celery seeds.\n\nChoose the substitute based on the particular dish and your flavor preferences!",
